---------- Forwarded message ---------
From: Sylvia Yong-Gonzales <sylvia@livelyphysio.com.au>
Date: Mon, 26 June 2023, 12:28 pm
Subject: Team changes
To: The WP Perk Support Team <support@wpperk.com>


Hi There,

Please make the below team changes blurb and photo

1. Cecilia Sun : In 2017, she completed a Bachelor of Health Science and went on to complete a Masters of Physiotherapy in 2019 at University of Sydnay. In 2022, she completed APPI Pilates (a course for physios only) and both level 1 and level 2 Dry Needling courses.

Cecilia has worked mainly in private clinics in the past four years. In her practice, Cecilia believes in evidence-based practices, and she looks forward to assisting her clients to accomplish their individual goals.

In Cissy's spare time, she likes working out at the gym and taking a variety of fitness classes, such as weight training, yoga, and Pilates. She believes exercise is a cure in any emotional state, because it refreshes and recharges her.

Cecilia speaks fluent Mandarin and English.

Cecilia works part-time and provides physio on Monday-Wednesday. She teaches PEP on Monday afternoons, Tuesday & Saturday mornings.

2. Nini Dai : Nini completed a Bachelor degree in Rehabilitation and went on to complete a Master of Physiotherapy degree at University of Sydney. She values patient-centered care and believes that self-empowerment, education & goal setting are crucial in achieving the best outcomes for rehabilitation. Nini is sure to provide the most evidence-based practice to improve each patient's condition.

Nini has special interest in sports-related injuries & is going to be learning more to help with women's health pathologies. She is a qualified GEMt Dry Needling practitioner and a qualified Pilates instructor for mat and studio pilates. She is on her way to Polestar Pilates Australia to become a Certified Pilates Practitioner in Rehabilitation. She has committed to learn more physiotherapy techniques including Muscle energy, the Thoracic Ring Approach and ConnectTherapyTM , which will be completed at the end of 2023.

In Nini's spare time, she enjoys playing basketball and badminton, reading books, spending time with friends and family, and playing the piano.

Apart from English, Nini can also speak fluent Mandarin.

Nini provides physio treatments on Wednesday - Friday and teaches PEP on Wednesday afternoon, Friday & Saturday morning.

3. Katrina Lewis : new pic
4. Julie Vawdrey : new pic
5. Christina Lorenc (nee munton) : new pic
6. Sally Ting : new pic

Sally works part-time. She is available for Physiotherapy treatment on Monday & Thursday afternoons and Wednesday all day. She teaches PEP on Monday mornings.

7. Oor Na Chiangmai :

Oor is trained by a Multiple Award Winner Spa including the Best Boutique Spa in Asia 2022 - Zira Spa, Chiangmai Thailand. She is a Qualified Remedial Massage Therapist trained in Australia (Meadowbank TAFE, NSW) and a Qualified Thai and Swedish Massage Therapist trained in Thailand.

Oor is also trained and qualified to provide Stone Therapy Massage, Aromatherapy Massage, Indian Head Massage for Relaxation, Reflexology for Relaxation and Superficial Lymph Massage Treatment. Oor is undertaking postgraduate course, a Certificate of Pregnancy Massage facilitated by Pregnancy Massage Australia. She is offering Pregnancy Massage for Trimester 1-2-3.

Oor believes in a holistic approach and carefully designs each treatment session to suit individual condition, fitness and preference.

On her day off (from Lively), Oor is welcoming clients at her private boutique day spa in Central Coast NSW - Spa View Killcare. Oor loves to travel to different parts of the world and enjoys different cuisines. She relaxes through Vipassana meditation, yoga, swimming and bush walking with friends.

Oor works on Thursdays.

8. Alissa Antoon : new pic
9: Sarah Gartside
Sarah works on Monday & Saturday, and once a month Friday.

10. Nikita Rao : new pic


Thank you Rica.

Regards,
Sylvia Yong-Gonzales
